This paper proposes a novel algorithm for training large-scale graph convolutional networks (GCN) that is computationally efficient and memory-efficient. The paper focuses on the application of GCN to graph-based problems, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the scalability of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it may be relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper includes experiments on the PPI dataset, which is related to computer vision, indicating that it may also be relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
